<h3>About Your Weaver Site: </h3>
<ul><h1><a href="">{$site.names|get(0)}</a></h1></ul>

<p class="important">
We notice that you’ve had Weaver for a while and haven’t created any workspaces. 
We encourage you TO EXPERIMENT WITH WEAVER!
</p>


<p>Workspaces are where people do the work, and you can create as many as you want.</p> 
 
<p>Need some hints on how to start?  Try watching the video: 
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=KX13p4rnhb0&list=PL-y45TQ2Eb40eQWwH5NjyIjgepk_MonlB&index=2">Workspaces: How to Create in Weaver</a> 
and at the same time familiarize yourself with other 
<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=sSJPN5XRFsY&list=PL-y45TQ2Eb40eQWwH5NjyIjgepk_MonlB"> Weaver Training Videos</a>. </p>


<p>You can access your site at any time using one of the following links.   We recommend you bookmark one of these links right away:</p>
<ul>
<li><a href="{$baseUrl}v/{$site.key}/$/SiteWorkspaces.htm">Workspaces</a> - go to this link to create your first workspace. Click on Options (in the upper right corner of your screen) and select Create a Workspace.</li>
<li><a href="{$baseUrl}v/{$site.key}/$/SiteAdmin.htm">Site Admin</a> - the configuration options for the owner (you)</li>
<li><a href="{$baseUrl}v/{$site.key}/$/SiteRoles.htm">Roles</a> - the roles (user groups) for the entire site</li>
</ul>

